<section class="section-light">
  <div class="container page-content">
    <h2>Journey<span class="dot-accent">.</span></h2>

    <h3>Phase 1 — Childhood & Training</h3>
    <p>Born between Brittany and Ireland, growing up crossing the sea by boat. Entered the ENSM (National Maritime Academy) in Marseille in 2010.</p>

    <h3>Phase 2 — Navigation (2010-2017)</h3>
    <p>From cadet to Second Mate at 25. Construction vessels, submarine cable laying (Sabella hydrotidal EMR), French Navy missions, worldwide navigation: Angola, China, Namibia, Mediterranean, English Channel.</p>
    <p><strong>Founding moment (2013):</strong> At Bourbon in Marseille, first confrontation with the abyssal technological gap in maritime data. Monthly paper-based data collection for ~600 vessels. This is where the founding conviction was born: technology and environment are inseparable in the maritime transformation.</p>

    <h3>Phase 3 — Entrepreneurship & Impact (2017-present)</h3>
    <p>Deliberate choice to leave the sea for a more global impact. Co-founder of VAIATA Dynamics (AI for maritime), General Delegate of GASPE (public maritime service), President of Fondation ENSM, lecturer in sustainable development.</p>

    <h2>Bibliography<span class="dot-accent">.</span></h2>
    <p>Formative readings that shaped the vision: from maritime strategy to planetary boundaries, from digital transformation to geopolitics of the sea.</p>
    <p><em>Full bibliography coming soon.</em></p>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
